##  Project Synopsis

This project analyzes the logistics performance of Magist,  
a Brazilian logistics service provider, to evaluate its  
suitability as a potential partner for Eniac’s expansion  
into the Brazilian market in 2018.

Eniac is positioned as a premium online marketplace  
specializing in Apple products and high-value accessories,  
where fast and reliable delivery is essential to  
maintaining customer satisfaction and brand reputation.

The main objective of this project was to assess whether  
Magist’s delivery performance aligns with the expectations  
of a premium business model. Since Magist primarily  
supports sellers offering lower-value goods, an important  
part of the analysis focused on identifying performance  
risks that could negatively affect the delivery experience  
for higher-value technology products.

To answer these questions, I conducted a structured  
data analysis using SQL on a snapshot of Magist’s  
2018 logistics dataset. The dataset included order  
information, delivery dates, product characteristics,  
seller data, and customer reviews.

Through SQL queries, I calculated delivery times,  
identified delayed shipments, analyzed the distribution  
of product categories, and compared the performance of  
technology-related deliveries with overall logistics  
performance.

Special attention was given to delay patterns and  
potential risk factors. Product dimensions such as  
weight, height, length, and width were analyzed  
to determine whether larger products were more  
likely to be delayed.

In addition, customer review data was explored to  
understand how delivery performance influenced  
customer satisfaction. The analysis also included  
identifying extreme delivery cases that could have  
a strong negative impact on customer trust.

The results showed that while most deliveries were  
completed on time, approximately **7.3% of all orders  
were delayed**, and technology-related products had  
slightly longer average delivery times (**13 days**)  
compared to the overall average (**12 days**).

A particularly critical finding was the presence of  
**24 extreme delivery cases**, where technology orders  
took more than **150 days** to arrive. Even though  
these cases were rare, they represent significant  
risks for a premium brand that relies heavily on  
customer experience.

To communicate these findings effectively, I created  
visualizations using Tableau to highlight delivery  
performance trends, delay rates, and review  
distributions.

These visual insights were then integrated into a  
structured business presentation developed in Prezi.  
The presentation summarized the key risks and  
translated the analytical findings into a strategic  
recommendation for decision-makers.

Based on the combined data analysis and visualization  
results, the final recommendation was to carefully  
reconsider the use of Magist as a logistics partner  
for premium products.

Due to delivery variability and extreme delay risks,  
the analysis suggested exploring alternative logistics  
providers with stronger capabilities in handling  
high-value electronics and maintaining premium  
delivery standards.
